      "role": "user",
      "content": "I see. So if success is relative, why do most historians and academics still use terms like 'primitive' or 'underdeveloped' when describing these non-Western groups? It feels like there's a subtle implication that because they haven't adopted Western-style bureaucracy or technology, they're somehow behind or less advanced on the spectrum of human development.",
